The silent footage documents indigenous people from polynesia and melanesia, including Samoa, Fiji, New Hebrides, the Solomon Islands, and Papua New Guinea. Later, in 1931 the film was edited with added narration by crew member William Peck.

The 1928 film 'Gow, the Head Hunter' was silent, narration was added in 1931,
